I’m so excited to turn this weekend's prop sale (collection of tabletop dishes, ceramics, kitchen tools and housewares) into a marketplace and highlight some of my very talented friends / great female entrepreneurs. Love seeing our local community coming together.
@havenskitchen, Alison Cayne, owner/founder of the Havens Kitchen cooking school and event space will be doing a book signing for her new cookbook appropriately called “Cooking School" on Sunday 11am-1pm. But we’ll sell her cookbooks until they’re gone! @jen_davidsonnyc, some of you know her as the GM of @barbutonyc, but she is also the creator of stunning handmade notecards. @hudsonandstella, my friend Judy and I go way back to our time working together at Calvin Klein. She now designs beautiful handmade jewelry. She will join us all day Saturday and Sunday until 2pm. @daniimcr, a talented NYC baker, is joining me to put on a bake sale both Sat and Sun. She’ll be making delicious items like Glazed Lemon Tea Cakes, Cranberry Crumb Cake and Hand Pies. I’ll be making apple and pear crostatas (aka pie!) and potentially a few other things. @tachechocolate, Aditi Malhotra, owner and founder of an artisanal chocolate company in the LES, will bring her gorgeous chocolates on Saturday.
📍199 Lafayette Street, 3B. Soho NYC. Nov 18-19, 11am-4pm. Preferred payments through Venmo, Paypal or cash. Just in time for the holidays, come join us for some shopping, meet these incredible women and enjoy some complimentary snacks (I might make a chicken stew on Sunday) and beverages. We’re all excited to see you this weekend.

I had every intention to travel all throughout 2017. Life gets busy blah blah blah and 6 months after an epic Patagonia trip I find my passport longing for new int'l stamps and myself dreaming of Paris. That trip is on pause, but Paris I'm coming for you soon.
However I am booking my first trip to Charleston next week. Make no mistake this is no consolation prize and I find impromptu travel really exciting. This a place I've dreamt of for years. Excited to get out and explore the beautiful city, eat amazing southern cooking and experience Charleston's charm & hospitality.
@laurenewe @explorecharleston I'm looking forward to a wonderful week with you! If anyone has suggestions for Charleston please leave a comment or DM me, really appreciate it. @tommyrwerner help a girl out 🙏. I cannot wait ✈️.

My classic apple pie with a new favorite milk pie crust. A nod to the Spring gods with a rustic flower crown surrounded by white quince branches. I made this at my Pie Baking & Styling Workshop this weekend. My heart is full from the company of the wonderful students at my first workshop.
Thank you @wfisher21 @natalie_perera @marjaharmony @bakedideas @cloudykitchen. I had the best time and loved all your incredible enthusiasm and creativity.
A huge thank you to our wonderful sponsors @oxo @vermontcreamery @jacobsensaltco @aplatsf @ericksonwoodworks @greecologies. Pretty sick swag bag (some did say!). Most importantly a special thanks to the team that helped pull off my first workshop... @the.hawkes @hannahmadgelyons @madeline.chen @angelasanchez100x @dolbynoble. I couldn’t have done this without you, love you guys. xo jude {check out bts on my stories & sign up for my mailing list for future wkshops - I can’t wait for the next one, link in profile}
